post_cb({"46452012": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "45", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "4342498", "CreationDate": "2017-09-27T15:39:45.337", "LastActivityDate": "2017-09-27T15:55:21.650", "Title": "std::hash::operator() - where is exception guarantee?", "LastEditDate": "2017-09-27T15:50:21.800", "Id": "46452012", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>Where in the standard does it specify that</p>\n<pre><code>std::hash&lt;T&gt;::operator()\n</code></pre>\n<p>will not throw any exception?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><exception><hash><language-lawyer>", "OwnerUserId": "1555823", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_46452012_46452188_0": {"section_id": 4689, "quality": 1.0, "length": 20}}, "n3337": {"so_46452012_46452188_0": {"section_id": 4498, "quality": 1.0, "length": 20}}, "n4659": {"so_46452012_46452188_0": {"section_id": 6084, "quality": 1.0, "length": 20}}}, "46452188": {"ParentId": "46452012", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2017-09-27T15:49:48.017", "Score": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "4342498", "LastEditDate": "2017-09-27T15:55:21.650", "Id": "46452188", "OwnerUserId": "4342498", "Body": "<p>This covered under [unord.hash]/4</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_46452012_46452188_0\">satisfy the requirement that the expression <code>h(k)</code>, where <code>h</code> is an object of type <code>hash&lt;Key&gt;</code> and <code>k</code> is an object of type <code>Key</code>, shall not throw an exception unless <code>hash&lt;Key&gt;</code> is a user-defined specialization that depends on at least one user-defined type.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So, as long as you are using one of the standard supplied specializations for <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/types\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">fundamental types</a>, <code>operator()</code> will not throw.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2017-09-27T15:55:21.650"}});